ğŸ”¹ Background

The Maratha Empire emerged in the 17th century as a powerful regional force challenging Mughal authority.

Founder:

Shivaji Maharaj

Important Developments:

Guerrilla warfare (Ganimi Kava)

Strong administrative structure

Confederacy after Shivaji

ğŸ“Œ UPSC Focus: Administration + Revenue system + Difference from Mughals.

ğŸ”µ Shivajiâ€™s Administration
ğŸ”¹ Central Administration
Ashtapradhan Council (Council of Eight Ministers)
Post	Function
Peshwa	Prime Minister
Amatya	Finance
Sachiv	Correspondence
Mantri	Intelligence
Senapati	Military
Panditrao	Religious
Nyayadhish	Justice
Sumant	Foreign affairs

ğŸ“Œ Peshwa later became most powerful.

ğŸ”¹ Provincial Administration

Divided into provinces (Prant)

Forts were key military centres

Direct control over land revenue

ğŸ”¹ Revenue System

Main sources:

Chauth â†’ 1/4th of revenue from territories

Sardeshmukhi â†’ 10% extra tax

Land revenue collected directly from peasants.

ğŸ“Œ UPSC often asks difference between Chauth & Sardeshmukhi.

ğŸ”´ Military System

Guerrilla warfare tactics

Strong navy (Konkan coast)

Fort-based defense system

ğŸ”¹ After Shivaji

Peshwas became powerful (Balaji Vishwanath, Baji Rao I)

Confederacy of Maratha chiefs:

Scindias

Holkars

Gaekwads

Bhonsles

ğŸ“Œ Third Battle of Panipat (1761) weakened Marathas.

